<br>
Anyway, without anything being filtered out, you should either be able to see the purple sparkles or the line &quot;A shadowed man staggers.&quot;<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that procs can be resisted, so if you are fighting higher level elementals make sure to debuff their MR first.<br>
<br>
I've seen my pet proccing on elementals in Twilight while waiting on some friends for a little romp in the Grey. Granted, with 53 air the fights generally didn't last long enough to see more than a proc a fight if that, but the swords were proccing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urabidsheep.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rabidsheep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(7/2/02 8:47:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=516.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsdown.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: well i see it like this...</span><hr size=1> Summon dagger (lvl 4) is the same as summon sword of warding unless you are after stats. Or if you are low enough lvl for the dmg on a weapon to boost attack of pet. Have you ever tried lvl 4 pet with a shadow men sword? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  with full plate armor<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  tanking red skellys getting hit for 1, hitting back for 16:P pretty good at lvl 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227830>Rabids Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showMessageRange?topicID=516.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td alig